The whole system modeling that is schematically represented in Fig. 1 has been resolved in MATLAB Simulation. The system consists of a PV module with a peak power of 200W, a DC–DC boost converter, and an MPPT controller circuit. The PV module is chosen to be with the numerical parameters as listed in Table 1 [12, 21]. The DC–DC boost converter is constructed as shown in Fig. 1. Finally, the MPPT controller is designed based on the proposed algorithm. Moreover, the proposed MPPT controller performance is compared with both P&O and firefly algorithms. The parameters for the P&O, the firefly, and the proposed firefly algorithms are listed in Table 2.Table 1
