				\begin{document}$${W}/{m^{2}}$$\end{document} the P&O records an output power of 192 W at 0.8 s, and it gets the maximum power of 201 W at 1.18 s after a delay of 0.38 s compared with the proposed algorithm as shown in Fig. 7.Fig. 7
The output power of the different algorithms for the given irradiance profile

